Sentencas: Apatite type rare earth silicates are being extensively studied as electrolyte material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC).
Titulo: Apatite type lanthanum silicate and composite anode half cells

Sentencas: In this paper we presents results on synthesis of Al and/or Fe-doped ATLS, the design of compatible anode materials, thermal expansion properties and co-sintering of half-cells from expansion matched materials using the advanced pulsed electric current sintering (PECS) technique.
Titulo: Apatite type lanthanum silicate and composite anode half cells

Sentencas: The issues related to the co-sintering of half cells have been addressed successfully by the combined use of nano powders and PECS.
Titulo: Apatite type lanthanum silicate and composite anode half cells
